About

These projects were chosen to be recognized as exemplars by participants in the OPEN Showcase Fair at the TAACCCT-ON! conference, coordinated by OPEN, the Trac-7 Consortium, and the U.S. Department of Labor (October 2014).

Projects were recommended as standouts in the following areas:

U.S. DOL Priorities

Strength in these areas aligns with the U.S. DOL's priorities for TAACCCT.

A rabbit representing quick progress.

Accelerated Progress

A compass representing guidance.

Career Pathway Guidance

A handshake representing support.

Student Support + Retention

A cursor on a human brain representing learning online.

Technology + Online Learning

Industry Training Sectors

TAACCCT is training today's workers to enter these growing industries.

A lightning bolt representing energy.

Energy Technology

Gears representing manufacturing.

Advanced Manufacturing

A globe with a westerly-facing arrow representing transport.

Transportation

A computer representing information technology.

Information Technology

A health cross.

Healthcare

Working Openly

The Open Professionals Education Network (OPEN) provides free support and technical assistance to all grantees of the $2 billion Trade Adjustment Assistance Community College & Career Training (TAACCCT) grant program from the U.S. Department of Labor. For information about TAACCCT, visit www.doleta.gov/taaccct.

To find out more about OPEN or about Creative Commons,
visit www.open4us.org
